> Finding yourself in a meatloaf rut? Enter: this sweet and savory version. First, we blend ground turkey with BBQ seasoning, scallions, and crispy panko breadcrumbs. Next, we form the mixture into mini loaves so everyone gets their own. The pièce de résistance? We swap out the usual ketchup glaze for BBQ sauce that's laced with smoky chipotle powder and tangy orange juice. Add sides of cheesy potato wedges and roasted green beans, and your routine meat-and-spuds dinner doesn't stand a chance.

== Prep ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; mince whites. Halve @Orange{1}.

== Potatoes ==

Toss potatoes on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%tsp}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet.)

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

== Meatloaves ==

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup} with 2 tsp water (4 tsp for 4 servings) until water has absorbed. Add @Ground Turkey{10%ounce}, @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, scallion whites, @Salt{¾%tsp} (1½ tsp for 4), and a pinch of @Pepper{}.

Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4). TIP: Wet your hands (or drizzle with oil) first to prevent sticking.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ Sauce{4%tablespoon}, a big squeeze of orange juice, and @Chipotle Powder{1%teaspoon} to taste. Taste and season with salt; add more orange juice and chipotle powder if desired.

== Roasting ==

Once potatoes have roasted ~{10%minutes}, remove sheet from oven. Carefully add green beans to empty side; using #tongs{}, toss with a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting; add meatloaves and green beans to a second, lightly oiled baking sheet. Roast on middle rack.)

Place meatloaves on same side of sheet as green beans.

Roast on top rack for ~{15%minutes} (you'll glaze the meatloaves then).

Once meatloaves and green beans have roasted ~{15%minutes}, remove sheet from oven.

Push potatoes together so they're overlapping; sprinkle with @Monterey Jack Cheese{¼%cup}.

Brush tops of meatloaves with 1 TBSP glaze each (save the rest for serving).

Return to oven until meatloaves are cooked through, glaze is tacky, cheese has melted, and beans are tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== Serving ==

Divide meatloaves, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Drizzle meatloaves with any remaining glaze from bowl. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.